General FAQ

This document is a community driven full breakdown of the respective class. This is a live document where we actively change it based on feedback and changes to the game to provide the best information to the community. The majority of us hang around in the Community Lost Ark Discord in our respective class channels. If you would like to give us feedback or ask questions contact us there.

Why should I play this class?

  • Wardancer is a straightforward class to play, revolving around her two buff skills and dumping all her damage skills in this buff window.
  • She has one of the best synergies amongst the DPS classes, providing both attack speed and crit rate to her party.
  • A variety of builds for both the back attackers and non-positional enjoyers.

How does my identity work?

Her identity consists of 3 orbs/bubbles/balls (up to 4). Hitting enemies with certain skills (normal skills) fill a portion of these orbs, allowing her to use another set of skills called Esoteric Skills, which consume a number of orbs on cast instead of mana. For that reason, Esoteric Skills are commonly known as spenders.

How do I decide on a build?

Both have their strengths and weaknesses. It’s a matter of personal preference.

Here’s a short summary of the builds. For further information, read their respective sections of this document.

Esoteric Skill Enhancement

First Intention

Summary

Utilizes Esoteric skills and the gauge system within the buff window.

Increases the number of maximum orbs to 4 and damage of Esoteric Skills by +8/10/12% per full orb at the instant of cast.

Utilizes normal skills with no gauge system within the buff window.

Increases damage by +20/30/40% but skills no longer fill up the Esoteric Orbs, which consequently make Esoteric Skills unavailable.

Pros

  • Expands on the orb management identity and the spender skills.
  • Higher burst capability
  • Flexibility between back attack or non-positional builds
  • No gauge management
  • Skill slot budget for a mobility skill
  • Front Loaded burst window
  • Flexibility between back attack or non-positional builds

Cons

  • Skills have longer animations and her bursts take longer to deliver their full damage.
  • Strict skill rotations on most build variations.
  • Dominion Fang + Conviction/Judgment management
  • Is able to maintain uptime, but it is required in order to optimize damage.

What are my Party Synergies?

Synergies are a buff your party benefits from. These only apply to your party and not the entire raid. Consistent synergies are up for most of the fight while Burst synergies are much more infrequent.

What are the key pieces of my build?

Runes

Esoteric Skill Enhancement benefits from Wealth Runes (specifically the second epic wealth rune from sea bounties) and high Specialization to build meter.

First Intention makes good use of Conviction + Judgment runes to help with Dominion Fang uptime.

Skill Points

While both class engravings have options to lower a skill to compensate for lower skill points, it is important to be able to gain access to utility tripods.

Why is Yearning important?

It’s considered a part of a build despite not being on your character.

Swamp of Yearning is used by supports and gives +8/10/12% Damage and Attack/Move speed to the party. This is a Relic Set they use that has a golden ring.

Why does Wardancer use Fate of the Lazeniths + Three Umar Families card set?

Three Umar Families: Back attack damage to foes +2% (6 awakening) + Back attack damage to foes +10% (15 awakening)

Fate of the Lazeniths: Elemental damage +2% (4 awakening) + Successful attacks create a chance of all Elemental Damage +24% for 8s (10 awakening)

Entropy Wardancer utilizes back attack elemental skills thus allowing this set to be effective.

Esoteric Skill Enhancement

Written by Morningbear, Ivxn, Tarnaz

Playstyle

Wardancer as a class revolves around the buffs,  and . Esoteric Skill Enhanced, or Eso, focuses on building as many esoteric orbs as possible before using an esoteric skill, or spender, within the buff window. This creates a rigid but smooth rotation.

Stat Allocation

Early Game it is recommended to play One Spender due to low requirements.

Late Game the build choice is up to you since you have access to much more stats.

FAQ: 3 Spender Hallucination

Can I run Increased Mass?

Yes. While 3 Spender Hallucination does not cap attack speed, while under Wind’s Whispers’ duration it is negligible. But outside of the window it can lead to dps loss so it will not be the main recommendation even though it is perfectly fine to use it.

What if I don’t have two purple wealths?

Refer to the table below for spec breakpoints and where to put the blue wealth.

What are the spec breakpoints?

Low Investment

1100 Swift

1100 Spec

Swift Pet

Mid Investment

1281-1350 Swift

1033 Spec

SSB / EC / MFK

1026 Spec

SSB / EC / MFK

Swift Pet

Best investment

1200 Swift

1156 Spec

Swift Pet

  • 1033 spec allows 3 ticks of Energy Combustion + Moon Flash Kick to hit 2 bubbles with 1x purple 1x blue wealth
  • 1026 spec allows 2 ticks of Energy Combustion + Moon Flash Kick to hit 2 bubbles with 2x purple wealth
  • 1156 spec allows 1 bubble to fill from one cast of Sky Shattering Blow.

How long can I hold down Rising Fire Dragon and how many esoteric orbs should I cast it at?

Because of the nature of Wind’s Whisper, it is better to let go of Rising Fire Dragon earlier in order to fit it in the window. Only with max attack speed can 3 spender hold Rising Fire Dragon the entirety of its duration. In the rotation given in this FAQ, you will be casting Rising Fire Dragon at 3 orbs.

My Energy Combustion doesn’t seem to have good uptime, what should I do?

First, you should not be using Energy Combustion off cooldown with this build. It should be used as close to the start of your next rotation but still be able to fill 4 orbs.

Why Excellent Mobility over Single Hit for Moon Flash Kick?

  • Lowers the rotation speed by moving from Moon Flash Kick as the bottleneck to  Wind’s Whisper being the bottleneck (22s -> 21s).
    - Allows flexibility on the damage gem for     Moon Flash Kick to be able to used as a cd gem for Rising Fire Dragon which enables more flexibility when it is not able to landed within Wind’s Whispers’ Ready Attack window.
  • Allows the tripod budget to go to  Roar of Courage’s gauge gen tripod for an easier orb economy.

I can increase my cooldown gems now, what is the priority and the maximum distribution to keep the rotation synced?

From highest to lowest priority:

 Wind’s Whisper, level 10

 Roar of Courage and  Blast Formation, level 8

 Sky Shattering Blow, level 8+

 Energy Combustion, as high as possible

FAQ: 4 Spender Hallucination

Can I run this build right now?

Yes. With 1700+ spec the rotation is functional. 1712 spec is for  RoC + 3 tick  EC 2 bubble, and 1793 spec is for  SSB + 4 tick  EC 2 bubble. Aim for 1793 if you can.

How is this different from 4 Spender Entropy?

This plays similarly in its rotations, but is able to start its rotations off cooldown at any time due to its hit master nature. In exchange for high damage, it becomes easier to pilot and may lead to higher raid performance depending on the pilot.

RFD Tenacity vs Lucky Bubble?

As this is a tripod that will be left at level 1, you may use either one based on preference. In cases where you have high  EC uptime, you will not be needing the lucky bubble tripod.

SI Lucky bubble vs ready attack?

 Ready Attack has higher damage potential in raids, but it is more recommended to go Lucky Bubble as the rotation is more flexible and has higher damage potential in a small window due to Roar of Courage.

Theoretical max damage combo is to full hold Rising Fire Dragon within Wind’s Whisper when at max attack speed and then Spiral Impact after in Roar of Courage + Sky Shattering Blow’s Ready Attack. It is therefore not worth it to take Ready Attack if playing to attempt this rotation.

 

How is the playstyle different from 3 spender Hallucination?

With access to spiral impact’s ready attack buff, you are not tied to ww as the sole damage window and can play around two different burst rotations.

I can increase my cooldown gems now, what is the priority and the maximum distribution to keep the rotation synced?

From highest to lowest priority:

 Wind’s Whisper, level 10

 Roar of Courage and  Blast Formation, level 8

 Sky Shattering Blow, level 8-10

Less priority than Sky Shattering blow, but ideally match the cd gem levels.

 Energy Combustion, as high as possible

FAQ: 4 Spender Entropy

Can I run this build right now?

Yes. With 1712+ spec the rotation is functional. 1712 spec is for  RoC + 3 tick  EC 2 bubble, and 1793 spec is for  SSB + 4 tick  EC 2 bubble. Aim for 1793 if you can.

Does this build do a lot of damage?

Yes IF you have max awakening Lazenith and Umar's card sets. Without this card set at max the build will perform suboptimally. Even with the card set, anytime you mess up a Lazenith proc is a massive DPS loss.

RFD Tenacity vs Lucky Bubble?

As this is a tripod that will be left at level 1, you may use either one based on preference. In cases where you have high EC uptime, you will not be needing the lucky bubble tripod.

SI Lucky bubble vs ready attack?

Ready attack requires a level 5 tripod while lucky bubble does not. This limits the tripod budget while being around the same damage per cycle under the condition that the card set LazUmar is being used. Ready attack has higher damage potential in raids, but it is more recommended to opt for a qol tripod instead.

Swap the Blessing of the Wind level 5 or Extensive Combustion level 5 tripod to level 1 to level Ready Attack to level 5 if using it.

How is the playstyle different from Hallucination builds?

Due to the nature of Laz/Umar's card set, you must avoid proccing the card set outside of your rotation. As the build is optimized around back attacking, not doing so or holding skills for too long may lead to dealing less damage than how much Hallucination builds would have dealt otherwise.

How should I execute the burst with LazUmar?

The same as the rotation listed in the rotation section. As  RFD does 150% damage when full held vs tap, it is okay to leave out  RFD of the main rotation even when Laz is up for that cycle. Aim to just land the skill within your given burst window!

Can I use a Spec+Crit bracelet?

Yes, Spec+Crit is higher damage per cycle, but Spec+Swift offers better LazUmar management as well as noticeable attack speed for the main rotation hence why it is recommended more.

I can increase my cooldown gems now, what is the priority and the maximum distribution to keep the rotation synced?

From highest to lowest priority:

 Wind’s Whisper, level 10

 Roar of Courage and  Blast Formation, level 8

 Sky Shattering Blow, level 8-10

Less priority than Sky Shattering blow, but ideally match the cd gem levels.

 Energy Combustion, as high as possible

Which build does the most damage in Trixion?

4 Spender Entropy > 3 Spender Entropy (w/ LazUmar) > 4 Spender Hallucination > 3 Spender Hallucination

While the last 4 builds listed are ranked in Trixion damage, their damage is actually not that different in actual raids and is mainly dependent on the player.

Which build has the biggest uptime on synergies?

3 Spender Hallucination (6s/12-14s) > 4 Spender Hallucination (6s/14-16s) > 4 Spender Entropy (6s/16-18s)

Why are 1 spender and 2 spender no longer recommended?

  • The latest express pass is now up to 1540 and gives a free 5x3 engraving setup while allowing the player to select high quality accessories for the build.
  • 2 spender was recommended because of the low threshold to play the build efficiently be it runes, stats, or skill points.
  • 1 spender was a great build before relic set, and due to how easy it is for new and old players both to be able to get up to 1460 ilevels, it is no longer relevant.

If seeking a consistent damage build, 3 spender hallucination is recommended as it is an upgraded version of the 2 spender playstyle as long as it is highly invested (gems + swift/spec stats).

First Intention

Written by Gradeus, Loyalar, Carried

Playstyle

First Intention is the simpler build for Wardancers. It does away with Esoteric Orb management and focuses on comfort, speed and reliability.

Similarly to Esoteric, it focuses on the Wind’s Whisper and Roar of Valor buffs to dish out high damage on your non-esoteric skills.

Gear Set

First Intention differs from most other classes, as it runs a mix of sets that can be slightly adjusted to your preference.

Dominion 4 + Nightmare 2 is a popular choice as it solves your mana issues.

Dominion 6 is kitted towards slightly more damage, an extra awakening charge and a faster spacebar but can have mana issues.

Dominion 2 + Entropy 2 + Nightmare 2 is the standard back attack variant

In depth look

The rotation is build on relatively simple principles:

  • Remember to activate your relic set by casting your awakening skill.
  • keep EC active and make sure it explodes on the boss.
  • RoC into WW to activate your burst window, in that order.
  • Make sure at least SK and MFK land inside this window, preferably FHF as well.
  • Fill the rest of the time with SSB to activate AP buff into FHF.

FAQ: First Intention

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

What level of cooldown gems should we have?

 - lv7 (higher = better)

 - lv5 (within 3s of SK)

 - lv7 (same as SK gem)

 - lv5 (depends on Quick Prep level)

 - lv5 (until 2 Dominion, then remove)

This baseline of gem levels will make everything sync within 1 second of each other (1400 Swiftness). Later on, you will also need to do more tinkering to make everything sync up, most notably building a decent cooldown gem for MFK. Sweeping Kick will become your hard bottleneck and most important gem later on with a proper build, alongside Roar if you want the extra duration, as they share the same base cooldown.

Energy Combustion Optimization

Energy Combustion is a skill that deals damage periodically around you. Since it is a normal skill, the First Intention engraving buffs the damage on this, making it a key part of our damage done in raids.

Thus, it is important to understand how it works, and how to improve your rotation around it.

Both of these tripods feed into each other, making it important to optimize damage based on how it changes Energy Combustion (EC).

‘Intense Battle’ gives a stacking buff that increases the damage of EC.

‘Last Whisper’ gives an explosion at the end of EC’s buff duration. The video below has tests on EC’s interaction.

Video proof.

In other words, EC’s damage calculation (Last Whisper) is only affected by the amount of Intense Battle stacks it has, at the time of explosion. This means that before the explosion, you want 5 seconds to build up 10 stacks of Intense Battle on your EC. The damage of the explosion is not built up over the duration of EC.

This does NOT imply that EC is not boosted by the Wind’s Whisper attack buff, but rather that it increases the explosion damage after it has been calculated.

What should I do between my skill cooldowns?

Generally, stay close to the boss to get EC ticks. Other than that, you can auto-attack cancel (1, 2, any input buffer, 1, 2), use SSB to get a Ready Attack buff to enhance your EC, or just dodge.

What’s an input buffer (for auto-attack canceling)?

An input buffer generally just means any movement from your character to cancel them out of continuing the chain of attacks. You can click away from your character then tap your attack key again, on top of your character, hold your movement key, etc. Whatever helps your rhythm.

We use an input buffer because it’s faster than waiting for your character to wind their fists down.

Why auto cancel?

Aside from looking cool, it also allows you to have a generous window to move out of incoming attacks. Additionally, it does more damage than just holding down your attack key and finishing the entire chain of attacks, which end with kicks that will lock you in place. We want to be fluid and quick enough to leave our animations ASAP, so having this bit of player input helps you improve your Wardancer gameplay.

What other tips can you give?

  • You can SSB + Spacebar to gain a lot of distance. Don’t use SSB twice if you wish to use it as so.
  • Your spacebar dash should be used often to reposition in fights, and can be used to chain with other movement skills to gain distance and change angles.
  • If you have SHD and are using it for Judgment/Conviction, use it before FHF in your WW + ROC window when Judgment/Conviction is on cooldown for more damage output.
  • Use Sweeping Kick first. It deals the most damage, has the longest windup and doesn’t displace you as much as Moon Flash Kick.
  • Don’t be afraid to counter! We have one of the best in the game on a very low cooldown.
  • Even if you are not running the Ambush Master build, we still do have a lot of movement speed and fluidity. Hit the back, it gives you more damage.
  • You have the best imprisonment breaking tools in the game, usually just auto canceling with EC ticks is enough to break someone out quickly, and SHD can free multiple people all by itself.
  • Once you have 1.5k+ Swiftness and are running the 2-piece dominion set, you have enough skill cooldown to use your WW + ROC timed with your EC explosion, ultimately making you not have to worry about holding your buff window for the bigger burst.
